msg.text: -- E5G_DR_DSP: comp '$$s': Loop found in forming shiftchain for DSP.\n
DSP comp '$$s' with SRI=GND cannot be placed at site '$$s'.\n
DSP comp '$$s' cannot be placed at incompatible site '$$s'.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' with different modes cannot be placed in one DSP block.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' with incompatible types (but same dsp mode) are placed in one DSP block.\n
DSP: conflicting placement of DSP comps '$$s'(#span=$$d site='$$s') and '$$s'(site='$$s).\n
More than 4 RST signals were found in DSP block $$d.\n
More than 4 CE signals were found in DSP block $$d.\n
More than 4 CLK signals were found in DSP block $$d.\n
DSP comp '$$s' cannot be placed at site '$$s' due to conflicting signal '$$s' and '$$s' used by other comps in same DSP block.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' cannot be placed at adjacent sites due to conflicting SIGNEDAB.\n
DSP comp $$s(site $$s) and comp $$s(site $$s) cannot be placed in same DSP block due to conflicting SIGNEDAB.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' cannot be placed in same DSP block; #Total MULT9ADDSUBSUM_ADDNSUB1(3) signals=$$d.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' cannot be placed in same half of DSP block due to conflicting SIGNEDAB.\n
DSP comps '$$s' and '$$s' cannot be placed in same half of DSP block due to conflicting ADDNSUB.\n
DSP comp '$$s' in shift-chain cannot be placed at site '$$s' (bad sequence).\n
DSP comp '$$s' in shift-chain cannot be placed at site '$$s' (bad interval).\n
DSP comp '$$s' cannot be placed at site '$$s' as that blocks other shift-chain.\n
DSP comp $$s driving more than one comp through SRO pin.\n
DSP comp $$s and $$s are incompatible and cannot be in one shiftchain.\n
DSP comp '$$s' in shift-chain cannot be placed at site '$$s'.
